last_episode_to_air.name: No Human Is Illegal
last_episode_to_air.overview: When a tough new judge takes over Pop's case, the family holds an early Christmas celebration, where big announcements and heartfelt gifts abound.

name: Gentefied
overview: Three Latinx cousins navigate their differences as they work to keep their grandfather's taco shop afloat in their rapidly gentrifying L.A. neighborhood.

episodes.name: Casimiro
episodes.overview: As their abuelo struggles to make rent on his Boyle Heights taco shop, aspiring chef Chris, artist Ana and father-to-be Erik face tough decisions.

episodes.name: Bail Money
episodes.overview: Erik wrestles with his pride as he tries to round up $4K in bail money before the baby's ultrasound. Ana hits up her Instagram followers for work.

episodes.name: Bad Hombres
episodes.overview: Chris urges Pop to spice up the menu with a taco of the week and goes all out to prove he's a true Mexican. Erik takes Lidia out for a fancy dinner.

episodes.name: Unemployed AF
episodes.overview: Pop tries to pull Chris out of a downward spiral, Erik asks Yessika for help saving the shop, and Ana scores a lucrative gig at a grown-up party.

episodes.name: The Mural
episodes.overview: Ana's mural celebrating brown love stirs up strong feelings in the neighborhood. Chris and Erik butt heads over how to bring in new customers.

episodes.name: The Grapevine
episodes.overview: Struggling to make ends meet in the mariachi band, Javier considers leaving LA with son Danny, who's in the throes of his first big crush.

episodes.name: Brown Love
episodes.overview: Nayeli interviews Ana and Yessika for school, a change in the shop's decor hits Casimiro hard, and Erik searches for a chance to pop the question.

episodes.name: Women's Work
episodes.overview: Ana's mom, Beatriz, reaches her breaking point when conditions at her job go from bad to worse. Nayeli hatches a plan to get to Bakersfield.

episodes.name: Protest Tacos
episodes.overview: When Yessika threatens to protest the food tour, Erik and Chris come up with a creative solution — and Ana finds herself caught in the middle.

episodes.name: Delfina
episodes.overview: Eric rushes Lidia to the hospital, Ana races to create a "statement piece" for her art show, and big news upends the family's plans for the future.

episodes.name: Welcome Home, Pop
episodes.overview: After three months in an ICE detention center, Casimiro emerges to discover he's a local celebrity. But life at Mama Fina's is not as he left it.

episodes.name: Vivian Castro Hates Mexicans
episodes.overview: Embarrassing flyers bring Vivian to the bargaining table. Chris flirts with food truck life. A business meeting stirs up confusing emotions for Ana.

episodes.name: Daddy
episodes.overview: To keep up with the demands of her new job, Lidia hires a charismatic assistant. Meanwhile, Erik embraces his role as a full-time dad.

episodes.name: Send Me A Sign
episodes.overview: After a setback at a deportation hearing, Casimiro asks his late wife for a message. Chris grows closer to Saraí. Ana parties with Bree's friends.

episodes.name: Yessika's Day Off
episodes.overview: On Halloween, Yessika hits the town in style, Nayeli and Ana pay tribute to their papi, and Saraí looks for a way to break the bad news to Chris.

episodes.name: Sangiving
episodes.overview: All Pop wants for Thanksgiving is a peaceful family meal. But when everyone's at the table, secrets, accusations — and even the turkey — go flying.

episodes.name: No More Band-Aids
episodes.overview: As Casimiro prepares for an interview on national TV, Chris and Erik have a trippy adventure in the woods, and Ana unveils her campaign idea.

episodes.name: No Human Is Illegal
episodes.overview: When a tough new judge takes over Pop's case, the family holds an early Christmas celebration, where big announcements and heartfelt gifts abound.
